description: Tourlami All Purpose Plant-Based Butter is soy free, nut free, and palm oil free, non-GMO, and kosher, with cocoa butter and coconut oil as the main saturated fats. Tourlami All Purpose Plant-Based Butter was formulated to work in specific applications for: cookies, cakes, ganaches, frostings, fillings, sauces, compound butters, and spreads. This butter can be clarified and works beautifully in sweet and savory applications. Our 100 percent vegan butter is a 1:1 substitution for dairy-based butter and will elevate the quality and taste of your plant-based products. Use this butter at room temperature, between 60°F-65°F.
name: All Purpose Plant Based Butter, Bulk

description: This pure avocado oil has a high smoke point, which means it's ideal for use in a variety of cooking situations. Use it to sauté vegetables for stir-fry, or you can pan-roast beef for your main dish. Put a little in a pan and grill up some delicious fish with a side of asparagus for a healthy, satisfying meal. Cube your favorite root vegetables, toss them in some Olivari Avocado Oil, wrap them in aluminum foil and grill for a flavorful addition to your table. The oil has a neutral flavor that will go well with any dish.

description: Kerrygold Salted Butter is a luscious, golden spread crafted from the finest Irish dairy. Known for its unparalleled quality and taste, our butter is an indulgent delight that adds a touch of elegance to your culinary creations. Savor the rich, creamy flavor that has made Kerrygold a beloved household name around the world. Our butter begins with the freshest, high-quality milk from grass-fed cows that roam the picturesque, green pastures of Ireland. These happy, well-nourished cows produce a milk that is rich in nutrients and flavors, setting the stage for an exceptional butter. At Kerrygold, we combine time-honored traditions with modern techniques to create a smooth, luxurious butter that is perfect for spreading, cooking, and baking. Our master butter makers churn the cream slowly and carefully, preserving its delicate flavor while adding just the right amount of fine sea salt to enhance its natural taste.
name: 80% Salted Butter

description: Gold Medal pancake mix is a high-quality mix that is perfect for making delicious and fluffy pancakes. This mix is made using premium quality ingredients, including wheat flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt, to create a perfectly balanced and delicious pancake batter. Gold Medal pancake mix is easy to use, and can be prepared in just a few simple steps. Simply add water or milk to the mix, stir, and then cook on a griddle or frying pan. The result is a stack of light and fluffy pancakes that are perfect for breakfast or brunch.

description: Finally, a gluten-free pancake mix that's simple to prepare and tastes delicious. Keep your pantry stocked with our gluten-free mix — a weekend breakfast essential — and enjoy tender, fluffy pancakes (or waffles) at a moment's notice. We love them plain or dressed up with fresh fruit or chocolate chips. Our mixes are carefully crafted in our test kitchen through meticulous taste-testing (it's a tough job, but we're up to the challenge!) and blending to replicate our favorite recipes. The result? description: A disposable pastry bag is a flexible and convenient tool used for piping cake, cupcake, or cookie dough, frosting, and other decorative elements. Made of food-grade, lightweight plastic material, these bags come in a variety of sizes and shapes to suit various needs. They are designed for one-time use, eliminating the need for cleaning and maintenance. description: Glucose syrup is a sweet, thick liquid that is commonly used in food production and baking. It is made by breaking down cornstarch into glucose, a simple sugar that is easy to digest and absorb. The result is a syrup that is sweeter than regular sugar and has a smooth, sticky texture. Glucose syrup is a versatile ingredient that is often used as a sweetener in processed foods such as candy, baked goods, and soft drinks. It can also be used to prevent crystallization and improve the texture of frozen desserts and confections. In addition, it is used as a humectant to keep food moist and fresh.
name: Glucose Syrup

description: Agar is a gelling agent that has been used in Japan since the 15th century. Agar agar is a plant-based gelling agent used in cooking and baking as a vegetarian alternative to gelatin. description: Nutritional yeast is a deactivated yeast product that is commonly used as a cheese substitute and is popular in vegan and vegetarian cooking. It has a nutty, cheesy flavor and is often used to add flavor and nutrition to a variety of dishes. It is a rich source of protein, vitamins, and minerals, including vitamin B12, which is often difficult to obtain on a plant-based diet. Nutritional yeast can be used as a seasoning, added to sauces and dressings, or sprinkled on top of popcorn, pasta, or salads.
name: Nutritional Vegan Yeast

description: Ascorbic acid is a naturally occurring compound that is often used as a food additive. It is a form of Vitamin C that acts as an antioxidant and helps to prevent browning in fruits and vegetables by slowing down the oxidation process. As a food additive, ascorbic acid is used to preserve the color, flavor, and freshness of foods, and is commonly used in canned fruits and vegetables, fruit juices, and fruit-based products. It can also be used in baking as a dough conditioner.
name: Ascorbic Acid

description: Introducing Felchlin Trehalose in Powder, a premium quality natural sweetener that is perfect for adding a subtle and delicious sweetness to your favorite dishes. Trehalose is a unique sugar that is found naturally in many foods and has a lower glycemic index than regular sugar, making it a healthier alternative. Felchlin Trehalose in Powder has a beautiful crystal-like appearance and a delicate sweetness that perfectly balances out the flavors in your dishes. It dissolves easily in liquids and can be used in a variety of ways. It is perfect for adding to baked goods, smoothies, or for using in creative dishes like trehalose granola or trehalose glaze for roasted vegetables.
name: Trehalose in Powder

description: Sugar derived from starch, can be used as a preservative in various pastry, ice cream and chocolate preparations. Its sweetening power is low and its technical characteristics are as follows: DE 35-40, 77.4°B, SP 45%, AFP 76%. Recommended use: The ideal substitution for classic sugar when making ice creams, spun sugar, crystallized sugar balls, vegan desserts and more. Our technical sugars let you completely control how their intrinsic characteristics are used in your products. You can choose their sweetening power, their melting point and their anti-freezing power to suit your needs. Production processes are specific to each sugar depending on its origin.

description: In Bavaria, Pretzels are the Holy Grail of baking. We take them as seriously as our Bier. So I’m proud to share these passionately crafted treats from my homeland with you so you can experience pretzels the way they were meant to be. Can you feel the love? Prost! A perfectly baked pretzel will be crispy brown on the outside, fluffy on the inside, and crunchy to perfection at first bite. However, if you are in a rush or do not have an oven handy, you may serve at room temperature. Prop & Peller pretzels are fully baked, you can just thaw and serve.

description: In Bavaria, Pretzels are the Holy Grail of baking. We take them as seriously as our Bier. description: This Oval Pecan Raisin Bread combines the sweetness of plump raisins with the buttery undertones of crunchy pecans. Free from artificial ingredients, additives, and preservatives, this loaf is the perfect base for a sweet ricotta toast with honey or a savory roasted turkey sandwich. Each loaf of bread from La Brea Bakery is the culmination of over 24 hours of patience and care, meaning that shortcuts have no place in this crusty creation.

description: Silver Gelatin is a type of edible gelatin that is commonly used in the culinary arts for its ability to gel and stabilize food and beverage products. It is made from collagen, which is a naturally occurring protein found in animal bones, skin, and connective tissue. Silver Gelatin is a versatile ingredient that is used in a variety of applications, including the production of jelly, gummy candies, marshmallows, and other sweets. It is also commonly used as a thickener or stabilizer in savory dishes, such as soups, sauces, and gravies.

description: Vibrant colors and natural flavors are the hallmark of Alipro dessert sauces. Produced in Switzerland, Alipro dessert sauces are always made direct from the fruit or ingredient, never from extracts or juices. These ease-of-use products can be used to top fruit dishes, ice cream sundaes and even for plate decorations. The bottles are microwaveable or can be warmed in a bain marie. Also available in Raspberry, Mango, Kiwi, Caramel and Chocolate, these sauces are the perfect complement to your next recipe. Try them in a savory application too!

description: The world's first Wild Hibiscus Flowers in Syrup.  All natural and deliciously edible hibiscus flowers in a cane sugar syrup. Each flower is hand packed into the jar to preserve their quality and shape. All of the natural vibrant color and flavor comes just from the flower.  They are cooked in the jar and vacuum sealed which gives them a long shelf life. Hibiscus flowers in syrup are a type of preserved flower that is made from the petals of the hibiscus plant. They are known for their bright red color, tart flavor, and sweet aroma, and are a popular ingredient in many types of cuisine. Hibiscus flowers in syrup are made by soaking the dried petals of the hibiscus plant in a sweet syrup made from sugar and water. This process helps to preserve the flowers and enhance their flavor, resulting in a unique and delicious ingredient that is perfect for use in desserts, beverages, and other recipes. Hibiscus flowers in syrup are often used to add a pop of color and flavor to cocktails, lemonades, and other beverages. They can also be used as a topping for desserts, such as ice cream, cakes, and pies, or used as a filling for pastries and other baked goods.
name: Hibiscus Flowers in Syrup

description: Red miso paste is a type of traditional Japanese seasoning made from fermented soybeans, salt, and sometimes other grains such as barley or rice. It is aged for longer periods than other miso pastes, resulting in a deep red color and intense, rich umami flavor. Red miso paste has a salty, tangy flavor that can range from mild to robust, depending on the length of the fermentation process. It is often used in Japanese cuisine to flavor soups, stews, marinades, and sauces, and can also be used as a seasoning for vegetables, meats, and fish.
name: Red Miso Paste

description: Aji panca paste is a type of chili paste that is commonly used in Peruvian cuisine. It is made from a variety of chili pepper that is native to Peru, called the aji panca pepper. The chili peppers are roasted, peeled, and then blended into a paste with oil and other seasonings. Aji panca paste has a deep, smoky flavor with a subtle sweetness and a mild to medium level of heat. It is a versatile ingredient that can be used as a seasoning in a variety of dishes, including stews, soups, sauces, and marinades. It is often used to add depth and complexity to Peruvian dishes, such as ceviche, empanadas, and anticuchos (grilled meat skewers).
name: Aji Panca Chili Paste

description: Dried apple rings are made from ripe and juicy apples that have been dehydrated to preserve their natural sweetness and flavor. These apple rings are a perfect healthy snack that you can enjoy on the go, at work, or at home. The apples used to make these rings are carefully selected and sliced, and then dehydrated to remove the moisture content, resulting in a chewy and flavorful apple ring. The drying process also concentrates the natural sweetness and nutrients of the apple, making it a perfect snack that's packed with fiber, vitamins, and minerals. Dried apple rings are a versatile ingredient that can be used in a variety of recipes, from salads and baked goods to trail mixes and granolas. They're perfect for adding a sweet and fruity flavor to your favorite dishes, and they're also a great ingredient for creating your own unique snacks and desserts.

description: Sambal Oelek is a chili paste commonly used in Indonesian and Southeast Asian cuisine. The paste is made from ground chili peppers, vinegar, and salt, and may include other ingredients such as garlic, shallots, and lime juice. Sambal Oelek is typically used as a condiment, adding heat and flavor to a variety of dishes such as curries, soups, and stir-fries. It can also be used as a marinade or as a base for sauces and dressings. Sambal Oelek is known for its spicy, slightly tangy flavor and is a popular ingredient in many Asian dishes.

description: Whipped cream stabilizer is a powder that is added to whipped cream to help it hold its shape and texture. The whipped cream stabilizer is made from a combination of ingredients, including sugar, modified starch, and dextrose. When added to whipped cream, it helps to stabilize the air bubbles in the cream, which prevents it from deflating and becoming runny. Using whipped cream stabilizer allows for whipped cream to hold its shape for longer periods of time, making it a great choice for decorating cakes and other desserts. It also adds a smooth and velvety texture to the cream, making it ideal for piping and other decorative techniques.
name: Panna Fit Whip Cream Stabilizer Powder

description: Sour cherry spread is a delicious and versatile condiment that is made from ripe, sour cherries. The cherries are cooked down with sugar and sometimes other natural ingredients, such as lemon juice or pectin, to create a thick, spreadable paste that is perfect for adding a tangy sweetness to a wide range of dishes. Sour cherry spread is often used as a topping for toast, bagels, and pastries, as well as a filling for cakes, cookies, and other baked goods. It can also be used as a glaze or marinade for meats, such as chicken or pork, or as a flavorful addition to cheese boards or charcuterie platters.
name: Sour Cherry Spread

description: Dulce de Leche is a caramel-like sauce that is made by slowly heating sweetened condensed milk until it becomes thick and golden brown in color. It is a popular dessert topping in Latin American cuisine and is commonly used in sweets such as cakes, pastries, and ice cream. The flavor of dulce de leche is rich and sweet with a hint of caramel, making it a delicious addition to any dessert or snack. It can also be enjoyed on its own, spread on toast or crackers.

description: Erawan Japanese Rice Flour is a type of finely ground flour made from short-grain Japanese rice. It is a gluten-free flour that is commonly used in Japanese cuisine to make traditional dishes such as mochi, rice cakes, and tempura batter. This rice flour has a soft and silky texture and a slightly sweet taste that makes it an excellent choice for both sweet and savory recipes. It is ideal for use as a thickener in sauces, soups, and stews, as well as for baking cakes, cookies, and bread.

description: This Organic Whole Dark Rye Flour is an undeniable must-have in any baker’s pantry. Combine with whole grain flour for a wonderfully hearty, complex bread or let it shine on its own!

description: Caputo 00 Flour Classica Blue is a high-quality Italian flour, made from carefully selected wheat that is expertly milled to create a fine, powdery flour. It is considered to be the gold standard for pizza and pasta makers, and is widely regarded as one of the best flours for making traditional Italian-style pizza dough. The Classica Blue flour is unbleached and contains a high protein content, making it ideal for creating dough with excellent elasticity and great gluten development. This results in a pizza crust that is crispy on the outside, yet chewy and soft on the inside. The flour also gives pasta a delicate texture and a consistent, silky finish.

description: Maseca is a brand of instant corn masa flour that is commonly used in Latin American cuisine, particularly for making tortillas. The flour is made from dried corn that has been cooked in an alkaline solution, a process known as nixtamalization, which makes the corn more easily digestible and increases its nutritional value. The Maseca brand is known for its fine texture, consistent quality, and ease of use.  It can be used in a variety of dishes beyond tortillas, such as tamales, empanadas, and other traditional Latin American recipes.

description: Matzo ball mix is a pre-packaged mixture of ingredients used to make traditional matzo balls, a staple in Jewish cuisine. The mix typically includes matzo meal (finely ground matzo), baking powder, salt, and other seasonings. To prepare the matzo balls, the mix is combined with eggs and oil to create a dough, which is then rolled into balls and boiled in salted water or broth until light and fluffy.

description: Specially crafted Kosher for Passover, this Matzo Meal offers a soft texture and earthy flavor perfect for the Seder. Unleavened bread is made on New York City’s Lower East Side using a family recipe passed down through generations from Europe for a taste backed by nearly a century of quality products. These matzos are then ground into a fine meal with grains slightly larger than that of a traditional all-purpose flour. Free from sodium and fat, this Matzo Meal is the versatile holiday hero. Use for a crispy topping on stuffed peppers or opt for the sweet route with banana walnut matzo pancakes.

description: A high-quality addition to any organic baker's kitchen, Central Milling Company Artisan Old Country 100% Organic Type 85 Malted Wheat Flour is a tan flour with some visible bran. This blend is a roller-milled mixture of hard red spring wheat and hard red winter wheat, which is then malted with organic barley to give the fermentation process a boost. With a high ash composition, this flour is hearty and nutritious with a flavor that falls somewhere between white and whole grain. Let this flour shine in artisan loafs as well as sweet treats like cookies for oven-baked goodness that’s hard to resist.

description: Organic 100% Whole Spelt Flour is one of our most popular specialty products. Spelt — also known as Farro Grande or Einkorn & Emmer’s younger brother — grows tall and has a hull just like it’s older siblings. However, Spelt performs much better in bread baking applications. It develops a stronger gluten network that will give your spelt bread greater volume than Einkorn or Emmer. Organic Whole Spelt flour can be a great substitute for organic whole wheat or all-purpose flour in pie and tart crusts. Also, Spelt has similar baking characteristics as wheat but can be a healthier choice since it is more water soluble than wheat, making it easier to digest.
name: Organic Whole Spelt Flour

description: Self-rising flour is a type of flour that is pre-mixed with leavening agents such as baking powder and salt. It is commonly used in baking recipes that require the dough or batter to rise, such as cakes, biscuits, and muffins. The leavening agents in the self-rising flour help to make the final baked product light and fluffy. Self-rising flour can also be used as a substitute for all-purpose flour in recipes that call for baking powder and salt.

description:
Sequoia has more bran and germ than most bread flours, so it needs an extra 5% hydration. For every cup of water that your recipe calls for, add in an extra tablespoon. 

We love Sequoia’s flavor in our hearth loaves! It's delicious on its own or blended with any of our bread flours.

For any recipes that don’t call for a strong bread flour, like focaccia, flatbreads, or enriched sandwich loaves, Sequoia performs beautifully.

description: Tapioca Pearls are small, spherical beads made from cassava flour, which is derived from the root of the cassava plant. They are most commonly used to make a popular dessert called Bubble Tea, where they are added to sweetened tea to create a chewy texture. Tapioca Pearls are often cooked in sugar syrup or sweetened tea, which gives them a slightly sweet flavor and a chewy, gelatinous texture. They are available in a variety of sizes, from small to large, and can be dyed to add visual appeal to drinks.

description: This flour is made from the highest quality Dark Northern Spring Wheat grown in deep volcanic soil. This high protein flour is designed for long fermentation or for the pizzaiolo that is accustomed to working with a high protein flour. description: Tapioca Pearls are small, spherical beads made from cassava flour, which is derived from the root of the cassava plant. They are most commonly used to make a popular dessert called Bubble Tea, where they are added to sweetened tea to create a chewy texture. Tapioca Pearls are often cooked in sugar syrup or sweetened tea, which gives them a slightly sweet flavor and a chewy, gelatinous texture. They are available in a variety of sizes, from small to large, and can be dyed to add visual appeal to drinks.

description: Matisse's frozen and sweetened raspberry puree is made from a blend of Willamette and Mecker (guaranteed minimum) raspberries harvested at optimum ripeness. The selected raspberries are processed into fruit puree in our production facilities. The pulp obtained is then de-aerated in order to eliminate any risk of micro-oxidation and is heat treated by a special, ultra-rapid ohmic heating process, which contributes to preserving all the organoleptic qualities of the fresh fruit (flavour, colour, texture). Then, the puree is frozen.
name: Raspberry Puree

description: The banana is not strictly speaking a fruit since its small black seeds cannot be used to reproduce the fruit. The banana tree is not a tree either because it produces no wood, but is in fact the world’s biggest grass plant, spreading through underground rhizomes. The banana has no seasons, but produces “fruit” year-round even if the original plant produced no fruit at all and had sterile flowers. The “miracle” of very nutritional and tasty “hands of bananas” sprouting from the plant occurred in South-East Asia during the Neolithic age, probably in Indonesia, but this evolutionary transformation remained an enigma for ancient botanists who called it Musa Paradisiaca, the muse fallen from the heavens. Since it had no seeds, its transposition (or perhaps transmutation) to Central America and Africa also remains a mystery, generating all sorts of sometimes outlandish theories, including the separation of the continents, unknown contacts between ancient civilizations and even extra-terrestrials. Having arrived in Europe quite late, at the end of the 19th Century, since it had to be ripened in highly controlled conditions, it became, along with coconuts and grapefruits, the most fashionable fruits of the Belle Époque in the Thirties in France, with the American cabaret star, Joséphine Baker appearing on the stage of the Folies-Bergères wearing only a skirt made of bananas. This purée is obtained by the strict selection and the blending of ripe fruit varieties harvested by our producers. This purée has been finely sieved and packaged in our Valence plant. Our production process guarantees an unvarying sugar content and acidity while maintaining as much as possible the organoleptic properties of fresh fruit.
name: Banana Puree

description: The lemon (the scientific name being Citrus medica limona) is a citrus fruit belonging to the Rutaceae family. Originating in Kashmir, it arrives in China almost four millennia ago, where it is known as limung. It then moves on to Persia and Asia Minor, before reaching the Middle East and North Africa. The Arabs, which call it li mûm, disseminate it all around the Mediterranean beginning in the 10th Century, notably in Sicily and, to the East, via Greece. The Spanish and Russians transform the name to limon, which English picks up as lemon, while in France it takes on the denomination of citron, derived from the Latin citrus. For their part, the Hungarians take on the French term, while the Poles call it cytryna. Its reputation as a medicinal substance comes from its high content in Vitamin C, which will be used to protect sailors from scurvy when at sea for long periods of time. The Chilean poet, Pablo Neruda, in the 20th Century will speak of the limón in his Elementary Odes as “a ray transformed into a fruit”.
name: Lemon Puree

Meticulously crafted in small batches, it embodies the care, expertise, and authenticity that define Boiron. Use it to create refreshing sorbets, craft vibrant fruit sauces, or incorporate it into cocktails and mocktails for a delightful twist.

description: Guava paste is a sweet, thick jelly-like substance that is made from the pulp of guava fruit. Goya is a popular brand that produces a variety of Latin American food products, including guava paste. Goya Guava Paste is made from high-quality guava fruit that has been pureed and cooked down to create a smooth, thick paste. It has a deep, rich, and sweet flavor that is both fruity and tangy, with a slight grainy texture. The paste is versatile and can be used in a variety of recipes and applications.

The ginger puree is made using only the finest and freshest ginger root, which is hand-selected and then carefully processed to retain its natural flavor and aroma. description: Shelf-stable mango puree is a delicious and convenient ingredient made from ripe mangoes that have been pureed and processed to extend their shelf life without the need for refrigeration. It has a smooth and creamy texture and a sweet, fruity taste that is perfect for a wide range of culinary applications. Shelf-stable mango puree is a versatile ingredient that can be used in a variety of recipes, including smoothies, cocktails, desserts, and sauces. It is ideal for making fruit purees, sorbets, and ice creams, and can also be used as a base for fruit sauces and glazes.
name: Shelf Stable Mango Puree

description: SICOLY's frozen and sweetened lemon puree is made from lemons grown in Spain. They are harvested ripe and then processed into fruit puree. The pulp obtained is then de-aerated in order to eliminate any risk of micro-oxidation and is heat treated by a special, ultra-rapid ohmic heating process, which contributes to preserving all the organoleptic qualities of the fresh fruit (flavour, colour, texture).

description: Its name today evokes a somewhat erotic notion, but its origin is rather more chaste, referring to the Passion of Christ. Its scientific nomenclature, passiflora, is an allusion to the vine that bears its fruits. Baptised Passion Fruit by missionaries in Brazil at the beginning of the 18th Century, it was used as a metaphorical tool to teach the Calvary: its corolla as the crown of thorns, its pistils as the nails of the cross, its branches as the instruments of flagellation, its five petals and five sepals as the 10 apostles, etc. This fruit, with its intense aromas, cultivated in Latin America, Africa and the Asia-Pacific region, is used both in savory dishes and in desserts and pastry, as well as in a great variety of drinks. This purée is obtained by the strict selection and the blending of ripe fruit varieties harvested by our producers. This purée has been finely sieved and packaged in our Valence plant. Our production process guarantees an unvarying sugar content and acidity while maintaining as much as possible the organoleptic properties of fresh fruit.
name: Passionfruit Puree

It is known for its unique flavor profile, which is a blend of tart, sweet, and citrusy notes, and is often used to add a bright and tangy flavor to dishes.

description: The mango is the emblematic fruit of India where it has been cultivated for 4000 years. Buddha meditated in the shade of a mango tree and the Kama Sutra proposes it as one of the most sensual delights in the art of love. Its Tamil name, "mankay" was transformed into "manga" by the Portuguese, which brought it to America and Europe. Today, mangoes exist in several varieties, with very different tastes, used in both savory dishes when unripe and in sweet dishes and desserts when mature. This purée is obtained by the strict selection and the blending of ripe fruit varieties harvested by our producers. This purée has been finely sieved and packaged in our Valence plant. Our production process guarantees an unvarying sugar content and acidity while maintaining as much as possible the organoleptic properties of fresh fruit.
name: Mango Puree

description: Its scientific name Rubus idaeus, conjures up the attractiveness of this fruit, which looks like a precious stone, and can be adapted to endless culinary ideas. Originally a wild mountain bramble, it has existed in the Americas, India and Europe for centuries. According to Greek mythology, its color comes from the daughter of the King of Crete who, whilst picking a white variety of the fruit, turned it red when her blood spurted from her breasts, scratched by the thorns of its branches. For Native Americans, the raspberry was used to make a very appreciated paste mixed with honey. In Europe, raspberries have been cultivated since the Middle Ages. This purée is obtained by the strict selection and the blending of ripe fruit varieties harvested by our producers. This purée has been finely sieved and packaged in our Valence plant. Our production process guarantees an unvarying sugar content and acidity while maintaining as much as possible the organoleptic properties of fresh fruit.
name: Raspberry Puree

description: The coconut was brought to Europe from Asia Minor by Marco Polo in the 14th Century and was simply called cocho (pronounced coco) in Italian. Derived from the word for head or skull in Spanish, the name is adopted by the French until the 18th Century and transformed into the current noix de coco and the English coconut (at first cocoanut), from the term used in Portuguese. The coconut palm tree can bear 10 to 20 drupes (and not nuts) at any given time and produces up to 100 per year. It is consumed fresh, when its flesh is still gelatinous, as well as at different stages when it dries, in pieces, grated or creamy. It is eaten raw or used in cooking, desserts, ice creams and pastries. Its water is used in cocktails, its milk in savory cooking and its cream and butter handily replace dairy fat, making it an essential ingredient in vegan dishes. Beyond its usefulness as a nourishing food, its wood, shell, husk, leaves and bark are used to make an endless variety of objects: walls and roofs of shelters, bowls, baskets, textiles and even jewelry and sculptures. This is why, in many cultures in Asia and the Americas, it is known as the tree of life! This purée is obtained by the strict selection and the blending of ripe fruit varieties harvested by our producers. This purée has been finely sieved and packaged in our Valence plant. Our production process guarantees an unvarying sugar content and acidity while maintaining as much as possible the organoleptic properties of fresh fruit.

description: Valrhona Pistachio Praline Paste is a high-quality, versatile pastry ingredient made with roasted pistachios and hazelnuts. description:
These Norohy Vanifusion vanilla paste represents the peak of vanilla expertise, making it an essential for any pastry chef seeking the purest product. Made with single origin vanilla beans from Madagascar, this paste is a skillful blend of vanilla concentrate, powdered vanilla beans, exhausted vanilla seeds, and cane sugar. The result is an astonishingly complex ingredient with earthy and woody undertones, so robust that there’s no need for flavor enhancers or additives. This all-in-one paste is a major time-savor in the kitchen, and organic certification means earth-friendly farming methods you can feel good about. Enjoy in a classic bourbon vanilla ice cream or opt for a decadent crème brûlée.

Recommended dosage : 5-10g/kg
name: Organic Vanilla Bean Paste-Madagascar

description: Neutral mousse mix is a versatile and convenient product that is perfect for creating delicious and light desserts. It is a dry mix that can be used to make a wide range of mousses, including chocolate, fruit, and other flavors. The neutral mousse mix is designed to be combined with other ingredients, such as milk, cream, or fruit puree, to create a light and fluffy mousse. It is easy to prepare and can be customized to suit any taste, making it a great choice for entertaining or adding a special touch to everyday meals. The texture of the mousse made from this mix is light and airy, with a smooth and creamy consistency that is perfect for spooning or piping into individual serving dishes. It has a neutral flavor that can be enhanced with other ingredients, such as vanilla extract or fruit puree, to create a range of delicious and unique flavors.

description: Piment d'Espelette Powder is a type of ground chili pepper that is named after the Basque town of Espelette, in France. This mild and fruity chili pepper is traditionally used in Basque cuisine and has become popular worldwide as a spice. The Piment d'Espelette powder has a bright red color and a slightly smoky aroma. It has a fruity and mildly spicy flavor with a slight bitterness, making it a great addition to a variety of dishes, including stews, soups, grilled meats, and fish.

description: This 1.5" Round Coated Chocolate Straight Edge Tart Shell isn’t just a major time saver in the kitchen — it’s also the key to that buttery flavor and delicate crunch sure to make any sweet tooth’s mouth water. description: Neutral mini cones are small, cone-shaped pastry shells that are made to hold sweet or savory fillings. These cones are typically made from a neutral-tasting dough, which means they do not have a strong flavor and can be filled with any type of filling, ranging from whipped cream and fruit to chicken salad or shrimp. They are often used for hors d'oeuvres or dessert, as they offer a convenient and elegant way to serve small, bite-sized portions.

description: Glucose syrup is a sweet, thick liquid that is commonly used in food production and baking. It is made by breaking down cornstarch into glucose, a simple sugar that is easy to digest and absorb. The result is a syrup that is sweeter than regular sugar and has a smooth, sticky texture. Glucose syrup is a versatile ingredient that is often used as a sweetener in processed foods such as candy, baked goods, and soft drinks. It can also be used to prevent crystallization and improve the texture of frozen desserts and confections. In addition, it is used as a humectant to keep food moist and fresh.

description: Maple Sugar is a type of sugar that is made from the sap of the maple tree. description: Dark Muscovado sugar is an unrefined sugar with a rich, complex flavor and a moist texture. It has a deep brown color and a strong molasses aroma, making it an ideal ingredient for baking and cooking, especially in recipes that require a more complex, caramel-like flavor. This type of sugar is made from the juice of sugarcane that has been boiled, reduced, and then mixed with the sugarcane's dark syrup. It is often used in cakes, cookies, and other baked goods, as well as savory dishes such as barbeque sauce, marinades, and rubs. Dark Muscovado sugar is a great alternative to white sugar, offering a unique taste and texture to any recipe.

description: This Fair Trade Organic Cane Sugar is a dose of sweetness you’ll feel good about, both for its deliciously bright flavor and its wholesome production. Hailing from sustainable Fair Trade farms in South America free from synthetic fertilizers, this sweetener is made by evaporating and crystallizing the juice from freshly hand-harvested sugarcane. This unrefined sugar packs a rounder and more complex flavor than traditional sugar, reminiscent of comforting molasses. Sprinkle on cookies and cakes to add an elegant touch, enjoy in your morning coffee, or let its sweetness shine in baked goods like scones and quick breads.
name: Organic Cane Sugar

description: This Organic Dark Brown Sugar brings a dose of sweetness you’ll feel good about, both for its warm, comforting flavor and its wholesome production. Hailing from sustainable Fair Trade farms in South America, this sugar is composed of delicate, fine crystals for a velvety and moist texture. Its deep caramel color gives way to a subtle molasses flavor that shines beautifully in gingerbread and oatmeal cookies. Use as a seamless one-for-one substitute for traditional brown sugar, perfect for baked goods as well as savory dishes like barbecued meats or baked beans.

description: This Vanilla Bean Gelato is proof that magic can happen when you go back to the basics. Hand-pollinated vanilla beans from Madagascar take center stage, while fresh, hormone-free whole milk and cream from Southern California cooperatives and pure cane sugar add that irresistible sweet, creamy quality. description: Bourbon vanilla extract is a type of flavoring made from the beans of the vanilla orchid plant, typically sourced from the Bourbon Islands (Reunion Island and nearby Madagascar). It is commonly used in baking and cooking as a sweet and aromatic ingredient. Bourbon vanilla extract is produced by steeping vanilla beans in alcohol, which extracts the flavor and aroma compounds. It is a popular choice for its smooth and mellow flavor, which is often preferred in desserts such as cakes, cookies, and ice cream.

description: Tahitian vanilla beans are a type of vanilla bean native to the South Pacific island of Tahiti. They are known for their sweet, floral aroma and fruity flavor with notes of cherry, anise, and caramel. The beans are longer and thinner than other varieties of vanilla beans, and they contain a high amount of oil, which contributes to their unique flavor and aroma. Tahitian vanilla beans are often used in desserts such as ice cream, custards, and cakes, as well as in savory dishes like seafood and chicken.

description: This Bourbon Vanilla Extract is crafted with only the best vanilla beans individually chosen from the lush, green island off the coast of Madagascar, making it a failsafe way to elevate your baking supply stock. A one-of-a-kind cold extraction procedure captures the full range of vanilla’s comforting floral and woody aromas as well as a collection of over 300 unique flavor compounds. Even just a few drops imparts unmistakably pleasant, calming notes to any recipe.
